HEADWORD: Inceptor
<hw>In*cep"tor</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>A beginner; one in the rudiments.</def>
<rj><au>Johnson.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>One who is on the point of taking the degree of
master of arts at an English university.</def>
<rj><au>Walton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Inceration</ent>⟦br⟧
